
  <sn><md>### Transaction {.text-center}

Transaction is an act or process of exchanging something, especially money, goods, or services, between two(individuals) or more parties (group).<br>
In simple terms, it means buying, selling, or transferring something.In another words give-taking or taking-giving relationship.

**Key idea:**

A transaction usually involves:

- Two parties (buyer and seller)
- An exchange (money, goods, or information)

**Transaction** is a process, but the virtue behind it is following rules and regulations to keep transactions fair. It also involves building trust so that people can confidently deal with me. At the same time, it means avoiding dealings with corrupt individuals and group.
</md></sn>
